Josepha is the mother of a girl who was participating in a dance class that NICA was sponsoring, and the leaders of that class were not supervising the girls very well.  As a result, many of the mothers were upset with the way things turned out.  Josepha came to discuss the situation with me.  She presented her case very fairly and asked questions.
Result: We came to an agreement at the end, and Terri Marlett apologized for not watching the project closer.  The agreement was that no projects involving young kids would be authorized without a vote from each of the parents involved.  No costumes or other benefits would be sewn without approval and involvement from the parents.  If the parents did not involved themselves, then the parents and kids would have to pay 100% of the benefit back.  In this situation, because the kids insisted on a style that was not approved by the parents or NICA or the leader, the kids have to pay 50% back.  If they choose not to, the loose future participation in IAP.  The parents agreed to this compromise.

Maykeling applied for a tutoring project, but due to using bad language and hitting other kids in her regular class, NICA had to deny the application.  Terri Marlett talked with her personally, and she cried because she was denied to work in the project with her friends.  She was told that if she improved her language and stopped hitting other children, she could participate in a project in the future.

Darwin, the computer teacher complained that a few students were calling him a faggot.  It was revealed to be Maykeling and Julio Picado.  The entire class was repramanded for the behavior and told that if any one of the students did it again, the entire class would loose the privledge of getting computer classes from Darwin.
Result: NICA does not reccomend Maykeling for a project at the present time.  NICA is still observing the situation and could be persuaded to consider her again.  For now, no project participation is available to Maykeling.

Result: Hola Dexter Gracias por escribir la carta de reconocer su error de mentir.  Yo le pregunte varios veces se era seguro, por eso estoy super molestada que me repitió la misma mentira varios veces. Quiero ayudar a alumnos que tiene la confianza de reconocer sus errors con dignidad y con confianza.  Estoy feliz que usted reconoció su error.  El proximo vez que le pregunto si es seguro, este es su chance de decirme la verdad.  Repitiendo la misma y después reconociendo ya no va funcionar.  Voy a conectar su conexión de internet.  Pero, si hay otro occasion que escucho o me mienta a me otra vez, va perder su conexión por un tiempo mas largo, como un mes o mas. La unica cosa que tiene en este mundo es su reputación.  Quiero que usted empecer de tener uno de honesto.  Cuando yo comento a Carla que paso, ella me dijo que si… "Dexter es así, siempre mienta por cosas así."  Este me dio un gran impression.  No se donde aprendió de mentir tan fácil, pero con la fundación NICA, esta cosa tiene que parar.  Nosotros no podemos ayudar a alumnos que mienta.  Tengo que tener confianza en su palabra como usted tiene confianza en mío.  Algo de pensar, si quiere un beca de universidad, tiene que reparar este reputación con Carla, Raquel, y Jamie de tener un chance.  Ellas son quienes que aprueban la becas. Gracias de nuevo.  Espero de que este es el ultimo vez que tocamos este tema.
